-- Starwood Capital buys real estate firms in Sweden and Norway for 11 bln NOK 
-- 
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 07:11AM EST
-- None



STOCKHOLM, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Investment firm Starwood Capital Group said on Friday it had agreed to buy Swedish real estate firm SveaReal Fastigheter and Norwegian real estate firm DNB NOR Eiendomsinvest I.

U.S. based Starwood Capital Group said in a statement it would pay 11 billion Norwegian crowns ($135.6 million) for the companies.  Starwood Capital Group last year bought seven retail parks and shopping malls in Sweden and manages over $38 billion in assets.  "We look forward to further increasing our presence in the Scandinavian markets as opportunities emerge," it said.